label: Low to High
short_description: Starting low and moving upward. Biases upper fibers.

label: High to Low
short_description: Starting high and moving downward. Biases lower fibers.

label: Low
short_description: Movement occurs at a low height relative to torso.

label: High
short_description: Movement occurs at a high height (e.g., Face Pulls).

label: Mid to Low
short_description: Starting at chest height and moving toward the hips.

label: Mid to High
short_description: Starting at chest height and moving toward the face.

label: High to Mid
short_description: Starting high and finishing at chest level.

label: Low to Mid
short_description: Starting low and finishing at chest level.

label: Mid to Mid (Level)
short_description: Neutral horizontal path – standard cable/machine line
